Eric M.  Teegarden, CPA
,


,

, Vice President, Chief Accounting Officer & Controller Hillenbrand







Mr. Eric M. Teegarden is Vice President, Chief Accounting Officer and Controller at Hillenbrand, a global diversified industrial company headquartered in Batesville, Indiana. 

Mr. Teegarden has been in his current role with Hillenbrand since July 2015.  Prior to his current role, Mr. Teegarden spent nearly eight years in controller roles of increasing responsibility within General Electric Company (GE), serving in a wide range of GE manufacturing businesses from appliances to lighting to jet engines.  Prior to GE, he served in reporting and accounting roles in two smaller, publicly-traded manufacturing companies.  Mr. Teegarden spent the first three years of his career, beginning in 2000, in public accounting for both Arthur Andersen and Deloitte & Touche where his focus was on energy companies and companies in financial distress. 

In addition to his role as Vice President, Chief Accounting Officer and Controller, Mr. Teegarden serves as a member of the American Institute of CPAs and the Kentucky Society of CPA’s. He was CPA certified in 2001 and serves as an advisor to the MBA program at Northern Kentucky University.

Mr. Teegarden holds a master’s of business administration from Northern Kentucky University, as well as bachelor’s degrees in business administration and accounting from Transylvania University in Lexington, KY.







Ulf Zimmerling
,


,

, Vice President and Associate General Counsel EMEAA







Ulf joined Hillenbrand as Vice President and Associate General Counsel in September 2013.  Before joining the Hillenbrand team, Ulf developed his legal knowledge and experience during more than 14 years in various leadership roles.  He began his career as an attorney in the fields of corporate law and M&A focusing on leading teams on cross-border transactional projects at the law firms of Clifford Chance and Allen & Overy.  Ulf subsequently joined Bayer AG’s HealthCare business to lead its legal M&A activities globally and was subsequently General Counsel at Intendis GmbH, Bayer’s global dermatology unit.  In his current role as Associate General Counsel for Hillenbrand Ulf functions as the counsel responsible for all Hillenbrand businesses, including Coperion, in Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and Asia (EMEAA). 






